definitions.definition: The organic chemical compound ethylene . The simplest alkene , a colorless gaseous (at room temperature and pressure ) hydrocarbon with the chemical formula C 2 H 4

main_definition: ( organic chemistry , IUPAC name ) The organic chemical compound ethylene . The simplest alkene , a colorless gaseous (at room temperature and pressure ) hydrocarbon with the chemical formula C 2 H 4
secondary_definitions: ( organic chemistry ) Any alkene derived from ethylene
